Package receiver

Class Receiver

java.lang.Object
receiver.Receiver
public class Receiver extends Object
The Receiver class contains some business logic. Almost any object may act as a receiver. Most commands only handle the details of how a request is passed to the receiver, while the receiver itself does the actual work. Concrete command classes will call the receiver methods with filtered legal parameters.
